Exercise 3:

fert = read.csv("Fertilizer Experiment.csv", header=TRUE)
fert$nitrogen_squared <- fert$Nitrogen^2
fert
##   Nitrogen Nit_by_20 Yield nitrogen_squared
## 1        0         0  24.5                0
## 2       20         1  41.5              400
## 3       40         2  52.1             1600
## 4       60         3  61.4             3600
## 5       80         4  73.5             6400
## 6      120         6  86.0            14400
## 7      160         8  92.8            25600
## 8      180         9  94.0            32400
quad_fit = lm(Yield ~ Nitrogen + nitrogen_squared, data = fert)
summary(quad_fit)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = Yield ~ Nitrogen + nitrogen_squared, data = fert)
## 
## Residuals:
##        1        2        3        4        5        6        7        8 
## -0.89532  1.84744 -0.14856 -1.78330  1.04322 -0.01998 -0.13815  0.09464 
## 
## Coefficients:
##                    Estimate Std. Error t value Pr(>|t|)    
## (Intercept)      25.3953155  1.0506461   24.17 2.26e-06 ***
## Nitrogen          0.7543938  0.0293719   25.68 1.67e-06 ***
## nitrogen_squared -0.0020766  0.0001548  -13.42 4.12e-05 ***
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## Residual standard error: 1.306 on 5 degrees of freedom
## Multiple R-squared:  0.9981, Adjusted R-squared:  0.9973 
## F-statistic:  1314 on 2 and 5 DF,  p-value: 1.571e-07
plot(quad_fit, which = 1:2)

library(car)

vif(quad_fit)
##         Nitrogen nitrogen_squared 
##         15.13909         15.13909
xvalues = seq(0, 200, 0.1)
newfert = data.frame(Nitrogen=xvalues, nitrogen_squared=xvalues^2)
predyield = predict(quad_fit, newfert)
plot(fert$Yield ~ fert$Nitrogen, xlab = "Nitrogen", ylab = "Yield")
lines(xvalues, predyield)

xbar <- mean(fert$Nitrogen)
xbar
## [1] 82.5
fert$Nitrogenc <- fert$Nitrogen - xbar
fert$Nitrogenc2 <- fert$Nitrogenc^2
fert
